President Obama has nominated Tamara W. Ashford to serve as a Judge on the United States Tax Court. Ashford is currently the Deputy Assistant Attorney General for Appellate and Review in the Tax Division at the U.S. Department of Justice. She has also worked in various positions related to tax law at the Internal Revenue Service and the Joint International Tax Shelter Information Centre. Ashford has an extensive legal background, including experience in tax controversy and litigation. She holds degrees from Duke University, Vanderbilt University Law School, and the University of Miami School of Law.